## 2. Data Model

### 2.1 New Entity: ProvenanceRecord

Persisted in PostgreSQL for long-term audit queries. During workflow execution, records live in Redis for real-time access.

```
ProvenanceRecord
├── id: String(36) PK — UUID
├── deal_id: String(36) FK → deals.id — links to deal
├── agent_name: String(100) — which agent consumed this data
├── tool_name: String(100) — which tool produced the data
├── tool_params: JSON — parameters sent to the tool
├── raw_response: JSON — exact response from the tool
├── timestamp: DateTime — when the tool was called
├── data_freshness: String(50) — e.g., "FY2024", "2025-03-08", "real-time"
├── execution_round: Integer — which iteration of the multi-round loop (1, 2, or 3)
├── claim_refs: JSON — list of claim strings in the agent output that reference this record
└── created_at: DateTime
```

**Redis key pattern during workflow:** `provenance:{deal_id}:{record_id}` → JSON blob with same fields. TTL: 24 hours (auto-cleanup for abandoned workflows).

**Relationships:** Many `ProvenanceRecord` → one `Deal`. Queryable by deal_id, agent_name, tool_name, and time range.

### 2.2 New Entity: ConsistencyWarning

Stored as part of `DealState` during workflow execution, and persisted to PostgreSQL on completion.

```
ConsistencyWarning
├── id: String(36) PK — UUID
├── deal_id: String(36) FK → deals.id
├── agent_a: String(100) — first agent in the contradiction
├── claim_a: Text — the claim from agent_a
├── agent_b: String(100) — second agent
├── claim_b: Text — the claim from agent_b
├── severity: String(20) — "minor" or "material"
├── explanation: Text — description of the contradiction
├── resolved: Boolean — whether downstream analysis resolved it
├── resolution_note: Text — how Red Team / Scorer handled it
└── created_at: DateTime
```

